t I have seen listed that is worth mentioning. I have been quading so long and I am just use to the way I do it that I dont use the staff to determine distance and if I starrted now, it would just screw me up. I did the quest it was fairly easy to do at level 31, but I am level 56 now, and I can honestly say that I have only used it once. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.docsmooth.com/images/dot.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/02 12:03:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=422.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.totalnetsolutions.net/nightwatch/images/head.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of Temperate Flux: Worth it?</span><hr size=1> why do you want to gain aggro as a wizard? (plus other reasons SoTF is awesome)<br>
<br>
1) you're better at it than anyone else.  Period.<br>
2) sometimes stuff goes bad and tanks are dead and cleric needs to be able to camp.<br>
3) drag-kiting.  a few melees (esp. rogue) + wizzy + open area + sow / boots = nobody gets hurt.  ever.  Wizzy opens with snare, maybe nukes once to be sure of aggro, then just start spamming your SoTF.  Rogue follows mob backstabbing, all melees whack at mob from behind, and wizzy just kites it without ever needing to cast again.<br>
4) manaless way to regain your quad from KSing dr00ds.<br>
5) manaless pullstick.  Makes single-pulling MUCH easier, because of low aggro of a single cast.<br>
6) pulling on the run.<br>
7) flux all mobs in a Kael raid for faction.<br>
